The paper focuses on the intersection of privacy and machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also discusses the practical implementation of the proposed framework, which involves communication, computation, and storage, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed scheme in the context of e-commerce recommendation, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
